This Presidential Memoranda, issued on December 21, 2018, delegates certain functions and authorities under Section 1238 of the FAA Reauthorization Act of 2018. The President delegates these functions and authorities to the Secretary of State and the Secretary of Homeland Security. The memorandum also states that the delegations will apply to any future public law provisions that are the same or similar to those mentioned in the memorandum. The Secretaries are authorized to further delegate these functions and authorities within their departments as allowed by law. Finally, the Secretary of State is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.